.SH CAVEATS
.SS Unsupported Declarations
The following types of declarations are not currently supported:
.nr step 1 1
.IP \n[step]. 3
Multiple comma-separated declarations are not supported:
.cS
int i, *p;
.cE 0
.IP \n+[step].
Only
\f(CWenum\fP,
\f(CWclass\fP,
\f(CWstruct\fP,
and
\f(CWunion\fP
names are supported;
complete declarations are not:
.cS
struct S s;                       // supported
struct S { int i; char c; } s;    // not supported
.cE 0
.IP \n+[step].
The C (and C++)
\f(CWalignas\fP specifier
is not supported.
.IP \n+[step].
C++ template declarations are not supported.
.IP \n+[step].
The C11
\f(CW_Noreturn\fP
(and \f(CWnoreturn\fP)
function specifier
is not supported.
.IP \n+[step].
C++ member functions that are
\f(CWconst\fP
and/or
\f(CWvolatile\fP,
or deleted
are not supported:
.cS
void f() const;
void g() = delete;
.cE 0
.IP \n+[step].
C++ attribute specifiers,
e.g., \f(CW[[noreturn]]\fP,
are not supported.
.IP \n+[step].
